cadDhcpRaMib.name: cadDhcpRaMib

revisions.description: Change default value of cadDhcpThrottleEnable, cadArpThrottleEnable, cadDhcpV6Throttle, and cadNdThrottleEnable from false(2) to true(1)
Increase range to full range of Unsigned32 for cadVrDhcpPdClientIaid and cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIaid
Add cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPSIP, cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPDIP cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPTime and cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPNum
Add cadVrDhcpPdCmMacAddress. Rename cadVrDhcpPdClientIpAddr to cadVrDhcpPdClientIpv6Addr, cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIpAddr to cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIpv6Addr.
Change description of cadDhcpRaLeasequeryVersion and cadDhcpRaLeasequeryMessageType to indicate both do not apply to IPv6.
Rename cadVrDhcpRelaySrcIntefaceIndex to cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceIndex, cadVrDhcpRelaySrcIntefaceLinkAddrEnabled to cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceLinkAddrEnabled
Added capability for DHCP Lease Query configuration.
Add support for DHCPv6 link-level addresses.
Added capability for DHCP Relay Agent Option 82.

cadDhcpRaMib.description: This MIB module defines objects to help support the Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol Relay Agent (DHCPRA) in the Cadant CMTS.

CadDhcpRelayAgentOptionType.name: CadDhcpRelayAgentOptionType
CadDhcpRelayAgentOptionType.description: DHCP Relay Agent Circuit-ID sub-option type. The value `mac-ifindex' indicates that the 4 byte MAC ifIndex is used for the circuit ID relay sub-option. The value `us-ifindex' indicates that the 4 byte upstream channel ifIndex is used for the circuit ID relay sub-option. The values `octet-string-text' and `octet-string-hex' indicate that a user specified octet string is used for the sub-option (with the -text and -hex indicating how the string is to be represented in the running-config).

CadDhcpPDPreActionDataType.name: CadDhcpPDPreActionDataType
CadDhcpPDPreActionDataType.description: type of data based on action. all - all prefixes and associated routes of C4 prefixOrIp - a prefix or an IP address cableMacInterface - All prefixes and routes of a cable mac interface

CadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType.name: CadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType
CadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType.description: DHCP Relay Agent MSO Defined Text sub-option type. The value `octet-string-text` indicates that a user specified octet string is used for the sub-option. The value `hostname` indicates that up to the first 64 bytes of the sysName MIB variable is used for the sub-option.

cadVrDhcpServerTable.name: cadVrDhcpServerTable
cadVrDhcpServerTable.description: This Table describes the assignment of DHCP servers to virtual router interfaces.

cadVrDhcpServerEntry.name: cadVrDhcpServerEntry
cadVrDhcpServerEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information related to the internet service provider.

cadVrDhcpServerIPAddress.name: cadVrDhcpServerIPAddress
cadVrDhcpServerIPAddress.description: Secondary Index into the DHCP server table. This identifies the DHCP server for this vrInterface/portType combination.

cadVrDhcpServerIPAddressType.name: cadVrDhcpServerIPAddressType
cadVrDhcpServerIPAddressType.description: This identifies the IP address type for DHCP server for this vrInterface/portType combination.

cadVrDhcpServerTypes.name: cadVrDhcpServerTypes
cadVrDhcpServerTypes.description: Indicates what type of traffic is served by this DHCP server.

cadDhcpThrottleBurstSize.name: cadDhcpThrottleBurstSize
cadDhcpThrottleBurstSize.description: Maximum size of DHCP throttle bucket.

cadDhcpThrottleRate.name: cadDhcpThrottleRate
cadDhcpThrottleRate.description: Rate in seconds between sending DHCP messages.

cadDhcpRaOptionType.name: cadDhcpRaOptionType
cadDhcpRaOptionType.description: The default DHCP Relay Agent Circuit-ID sub-option type if not specified for an interface.

cadDhcpRaOptionString.name: cadDhcpRaOptionString
cadDhcpRaOptionString.description: The default DHCP Relay Agent Circuit-ID sub-option value to use if the cadSysDhcpRaGlobalOptionType is octet-string-text or octet-string-hex.

cadDhcpRaOptionUpstreamChannelEntry.name: cadDhcpRaOptionUpstreamChannelEntry
cadDhcpRaOptionUpstreamChannelEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information about upstream channels for the DHCP Relay Agent TLV.

cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelOptionType.name: cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelOptionType
cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelOptionType.description: DHCP Relay Agent Circuit-ID sub-option type.

cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelOptionString.name: cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelOptionString
cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelOptionString.description: DHCP Relay Agent Circuit-ID sub-option user specified string.

cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelStatus.name: cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelStatus
cadDhcpRaOptUpChannelStatus.description: The status variable controlling row creation and deletion. CreateAndGo(4) and delete(6) are the currently supported values.

cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceIndex.name: cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceIndex
cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceIndex.description: This object specifies the selection of the layer 3 interface ifIndex of the SIP field in the DHCPv6 relay forward message. The default value is 0, which means that the routing stack will pick the appropriate RCM IP address. The options are cable MAC virtual interface ifIndex or a loopback virtual router interface ifIndex

cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceLinkAddrEnable.name: cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceLinkAddrEnabled
cadVrDhcpRelaySrcInterfaceLinkAddrEnable.description: This object specifies whether the link address of the source interface of the CM/CPE DHCPv6 message is used as a SIP in the DHCPv6 relay forward message.

cadVrDhcpRaOptionScnEnable.name: cadVrDhcpRaOptionScnEnable
cadVrDhcpRaOptionScnEnable.description: This object specifies whether enterprise 4491 (CableLabs) vendor specific information suboption (suboption 9) of the DHCP relay agent option (option 82) is to be populated with the CMTS CM service class suboption (sub-suboption 5) information for CPE DHCP requests.

cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType.name: cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType
cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType.description: The DHCP Relay Agent MSO Defined Text sub-option type.

cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextString.name: cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextString
cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextString.description: The DHCP Relay Agent MSO Defined Text sub-option value to use if the cadDhcpRaOptionMSOTextType is octet-string-text.

cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextEntry.name: cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextEntry
cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information about channels for the DHCP Relay Agent MSO Defined Text sub-option TLV. The ifIndex must be an upstream channel ifIndex.

cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextType.name: cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextType
cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextType.description: DHCP Relay Agent MSO Defined Text sub-option type.

cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextString.name: cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextString
cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextString.description: DHCP Relay Agent MSO Defined Text sub-option user specified string.

cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextStatus.name: cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextStatus
cadDhcpRaOptionChannelMSOTextStatus.description: The status variable controlling row creation and deletion. CreateAndGo(4) and delete(6) are the currently supported values.

cadVrDhcpRaOptionFanoutDisabled.name: cadVrDhcpRaOptionFanoutDisabled
cadVrDhcpRaOptionFanoutDisabled.description: This object is used to disable fanning out of CPE DHCP requests across DHCP servers on multiple subinterfaces by the DHCP relay agent.

cadDhcpRaLeasequeryVersion.name: cadDhcpRaLeasequeryVersion
cadDhcpRaLeasequeryVersion.description: Indicates which version of DHCP Lease Query is supported. This object does not apply to IPv6.

cadDhcpRaLeasequeryMessageType.name: cadDhcpRaLeasequeryMessageType
cadDhcpRaLeasequeryMessageType.description: Indicates the message type value of the DHCPLEASEQUERY message if operating in one of the draft modes. If the mode is rfc-4388, then the value for the DHCPLEASEQUERY message will be 10 and this parameter is ignored. The message type for the DHCPLEASEKNOWN, DHCPLEASEUNKNOWN and DHCPACTIVE messages will be the value of DHCPLEASEQUERY plus 1, 2, and 3 respectively. This object does not apply to IPv6.

cadVrDhcpLinkAddressTable.name: cadVrDhcpLinkAddressTable
cadVrDhcpLinkAddressTable.description: This Table describes the assignment of link addresses used by the DHCP relay agent.

cadVrDhcpLinkAddressEntry.name: cadVrDhcpLinkAddressEntry
cadVrDhcpLinkAddressEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information related to the DHCP relay agent link.

cadVrDhcpLinkAddressType.name: cadVrDhcpLinkAddressType
cadVrDhcpLinkAddressType.description: This identifies the IP address type for the link.

cadVrDhcpLinkAddress.name: cadVrDhcpLinkAddress
cadVrDhcpLinkAddress.description: Secondary Index into the DHCP server table. This identifies the DHCP server for this vrInterface/portType combination.

cadVrDhcpLinkType.name: cadVrDhcpLinkType
cadVrDhcpLinkType.description: Tertiary index indicating what type of traffic is served by this DHCP server.

cadVrDhcpLinkRowStatus.name: cadVrDhcpLinkRowStatus
cadVrDhcpLinkRowStatus.description: Controls row creation and deletion. Valid values are createAndGo(4) and delete(6).

cadDhcpPdRiEnabled.name: cadDhcpPdRiEnabled
cadDhcpPdRiEnabled.description: Global enable or disable route injection for DHCP Relay IPv6 prefix delegation. If set to true, then enabled. If set to false, then disabled

cadDhcpPdPrefixStabilityEnabled.name: cadDhcpPdPrefixStabilityEnabled
cadDhcpPdPrefixStabilityEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the IPV6 Prefix Stability is enabled or not. If set to true, then enabled. If set to false, then disabled

cadVrDhcpPdTable.name: cadVrDhcpPdTable
cadVrDhcpPdTable.description: This table describes the DHCP client information associated with IPv6 prefix delegation.

cadVrDhcpPdEntry.name: cadVrDhcpPdEntry
cadVrDhcpPdEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information related to the DHCP relay prefix delegation.

cadVrDhcpPdClientIpv6Addr.name: cadVrDhcpPdClientIpv6Addr
cadVrDhcpPdClientIpv6Addr.description: This identifies the requesting DHCP client IPv6 Link-local address.

cadVrDhcpPdClientIaid.name: cadVrDhcpPdClientIaid
cadVrDhcpPdClientIaid.description: The requesting DHCP client identity association identification number. One of the keys for cadVrDhcpPdPrefixEntry

cadVrDhcpPdIfIndex.name: cadVrDhcpPdIfIndex
cadVrDhcpPdIfIndex.description: This identifies the CMTS interface index associated with the requesting DHCP client.

cadVrDhcpPdCmMacAddress.name: cadVrDhcpPdCmMacAddress
cadVrDhcpPdCmMacAddress.description: This identifies the Mac address associated with the requesting DHCP client.

cadVrDhcpPdT1.name: cadVrDhcpPdT1
cadVrDhcpPdT1.description: The time duration relative to the current time, expressed in units of seconds, at which the requesting client should contact the delegating router from which the prefixes in the IA_PD were obtained to extend the lifetimes of the prefixes delegated to the IA_PD

cadVrDhcpPdT2.name: cadVrDhcpPdT2
cadVrDhcpPdT2.description: The time duration relative to the current time expressed in units of seconds at which the requesting client should contact any available delegating router to extend the lifetimes of the prefixes assigned to the IA_PD

cadVrDhcpPdPrefixTable.name: cadVrDhcpPdPrefixTable
cadVrDhcpPdPrefixTable.description: This table describes the IPv6 prefixes that have been delegated by the DHCP server and learned by the DHCP relay agent.

cadVrDhcpPdPrefixEntry.name: cadVrDhcpPdPrefixEntry
cadVrDhcpPdPrefixEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information related to the DHCP relay prefix delegation.

cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIpv6Addr.name: cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIpv6Addr
cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIpv6Addr.description: This identifies the requesting DHCP client IPv6 Link-local address.

cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIaid.name: cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIaid
cadVrDhcpPdPreClientIaid.description: The requesting DHCP client identity association identification number.

cadVrDhcpPdPrePrefix.name: cadVrDhcpPdPrePrefix
cadVrDhcpPdPrePrefix.description: This identifies the delegated IPv6 prefix.

cadVrDhcpPdPrePrefixLength.name: cadVrDhcpPdPrePrefixLength
cadVrDhcpPdPrePrefixLength.description: This identifies the delegated IPv6 prefix length.

cadVrDhcpPdPrePreferredLifetime.name: cadVrDhcpPdPrePreferredLifetime
cadVrDhcpPdPrePreferredLifetime.description: The prefix preferred time, in seconds, as received from the DHCPv6 server. A value of 4,294,967,295 (0xFFFFFFFF) represents infinity.

cadVrDhcpPdPreValidLifetime.name: cadVrDhcpPdPreValidLifetime
cadVrDhcpPdPreValidLifetime.description: The prefix valid time, in seconds, as received from the DHCPv6 server. A value of 4,294,967,295 (0xFFFFFFFF) represents infinity.

cadVrDhcpPdPreRouteInject.name: cadVrDhcpPdPreRouteInject
cadVrDhcpPdPreRouteInject.description: If true, then a route for this prefix and length has been injected into the routing table. If false, then a route for this prefix and length has not been injected into the routing table

cadVrDhcpPdPreExpirytime.name: cadVrDhcpPdPreExpirytime
cadVrDhcpPdPreExpirytime.description: The time, in seconds, when this prefix expires. A value of 4,294,967,295 (0xFFFFFFFF) represents infinity.

cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfTable.name: cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfTable
cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfTable.description: Cadant Virtual Router DHCP Relay Egress Interface Table

cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfEntry.name: cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfEntry
cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfEntry.description: each interface must be a unique network interface of RCM

cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfIndex.name: cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfIndex
cadVrDhcpRelayEgressIfIndex.description: This object specifies an Egress interface over which multicast DHCP relay forward messages are sent.

cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataIfIndex.name: cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataIfIndex
cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataIfIndex.description: cable mac VrInterface ifIndex - only valid when cadDhcpPdPrefixActionType is set to cableMacInterface

cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataPrefixOrIp.name: cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataPrefixOrIp
cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataPrefixOrIp.description: ipv6 prefix or IP address - only valid when cadDhcpPdPrefixActionType is set to prefixOrIp

cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataPrefixOrIpLen.name: cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataPrefixOrIpLen
cadDhcpPdPrefixActionDataPrefixOrIpLen.description: ipv6 prefix or IP address length - only valid when cadDhcpPdPrefixActionType is set to prefixOrIp

cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPSIP.name: cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPSIP
cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPSIP.description: The SIP of the last failed TCP connection between the CMTS and the DHCPv6 server during the bulk lease query process

cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPDIP.name: cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPDIP
cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPDIP.description: The DIP of the last failed TCP connection between the CMTS and the DHCPv6 server during the bulk lease query process

cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPTime.name: cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPTime
cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPTime.description: The time of the last failed TCP connection between the CMTS and the DHCPv6 server during the bulk lease query process

cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPNum.name: cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPNum
cadDhcpPdBLQFailedTCPNum.description: The total number of failed TCP connections between the CMTS and the DHCPv6 server during the bulk lease query process
